choices.text: an easy dismissal of a failed 20, 30, or even 50-year marriage, because they have already lived alone for the first 20 years of their lives. 110% agreed with the words: “You have to take care of yourself first.” In Dominica, the small number of men who do not leave their wives after impotency or infidelities are looked upon as weak, wimpy, and pathetic. A common reaction of callers to my radio show is, “Any wuss who would take back a wife after all that?” My reply: “Guys, don’t give in to the status quo. Remember, just as indifference and impotency are unacceptable, infidelity and infidelity are unacceptable, too.” However, that is not how society views the broken past of those couples who, for all intents and purposes, are broken. They prefer that those who do take back their wives are labelled “weak wimpy” and “pathetic.” This is the irony of cheating, discussed four months later and I recently had an excellent conversation with a married woman, undeterred by my advice but assured of her right to cheat. She felt healthy because men were nice to her. She asked me, “How do you wonder?” My reply: “Only when it works out.” Hurtful aside: “Undeterred” is a popular, hypocritical word in the region used to describe men and women who have brutally betrayed their partners of many
